OL,3,C'I was in Number 10 and a few months
OL,4,Clater I was in a prison van': Former MP
OL,6,F"I'd say (binge drinking) is probably
OL,7,Fa British disease," he said. "I would
OL,8,Fsay we were kind of brought up on it.
OL,10,F"It's not peer pressure, it's beer
OL,11,Fpressure. Am I am alcoholic, no. I can
OL,12,Ftake it or leave it."
OL,14,FSpeaking of his regret, he added:
OL,15,F"Hopefully I will serve as lesson
OL,16,Fothers.
OL,18,F"It took me 55 years to get on the
OL,19,Fwrong side of the law. I was a good
OL,20,Fcitizen who made a mistake and I own
OL,21,Fthe consequence of making a mistake.
